---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Pediatric CBD & Medical Cannabis Guidance FL | Releaf MD" 
  description="Compassionate clinical guidance for pediatric CBD and medical marijuana in Florida. Learn about state rules, qualifying conditions, and safe dosage with Dr. Kelly Ennix King."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="bg-brand-mint py-16 lg:py-24 border-b border-brand-primary/10">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center space-y-4">
      <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1 bg-brand-primary/10 text-brand-primary rounded-full text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider">
        🧸 Compassionate Care
      </span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark leading-tight uppercase">Pediatric CBD & Medical Cannabis</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Safe, reassuring clinical guidance for parents exploring cannabinoid therapy for children with qualifying medical conditions.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Content Section -->
  <section class="py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="bg-white border border-brand-primary/10 rounded-3xl p-8 sm:p-12 shadow-whisper prose prose-slate max-w-none space-y-8">
        
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark">A Reassuring Approach for Parents</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          For parents navigating severe, treatment-resistant pediatric conditions, exploring CBD or medical cannabis can feel overwhelming. At Releaf MD, we prioritize education and safety above all else. Under the guidance of Dr. Kelly Ennix King, we help parents understand how medical-grade, non-psychoactive CBD can be used safely and legally to improve a child's comfort and daily function.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          It is important to clarify that clinical pediatric CBD therapy focuses on <strong>non-intoxicating</strong> formulations (primarily CBD-dominant or low-THC). These treatments are designed to target symptoms without causing any psychoactive impairment or "high."
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark">Florida Pediatric Regulations & Process</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Florida law permits medical cannabis certifications for patients under the age of 18 (minors), but enforces additional layers of clinical and legal review to protect pediatric patients:
        </p>

        <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-3 text-slate-600 text-sm">
          <li><strong>Two-Physician Approval:</strong> Florida requires that two separate, qualified physicians evaluate a pediatric patient and agree that the benefits of medical cannabis outweigh any potential risks. Dr. Kelly will perform the primary evaluation and help guide you through securing the second physician's review.</li>
          <li><strong>Registered Caregiver Requirement:</strong> A parent or legal guardian must register as the minor's official caregiver in the state registry database. Only the registered caregiver is authorized to purchase, possess, and administer the medication.</li>
          <li><strong>In-Person Assessment:</strong> Just like adult patients, the initial consultation with Dr. Kelly must take place in-person at our Brandon clinic.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="bg-brand-mint/40 p-6 rounded-2xl border border-brand-primary/10 my-8">
          <h3 class="text-base font-bold text-brand-dark mb-2">Common Qualifying Conditions for Children</h3>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-xs leading-relaxed">
            Florida statutes permit pediatric certifications for specific, severe conditions where traditional treatments have failed to provide relief:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-3 space-y-1.5 text-xs text-slate-600">
            <li><strong>Severe Epilepsy & Refractory Seizures:</strong> Including syndromes like Dravet syndrome or Lennox-Gastaut syndrome.</li>
            <li><strong>Severe Autism Spectrum Disorder (ASD):</strong> Particularly when accompanied by self-injurious behaviors, severe aggression, or extreme sensory distress.</li>
            <li><strong>Chronic Muscle Spasms:</strong> Caused by cerebral palsy or other neuromuscular conditions.</li>
            <li><strong>Terminal Illnesses:</strong> Supporting comfort care and symptom mitigation.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-serif-headline text-brand-dark">Why Medical-Grade Supervision Matters</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          While CBD products are widely sold in gas stations and retail stores, these commercial products are completely unregulated and often contain incorrect labels, chemical solvents, or heavy metals. 
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
          Under Dr. Kelly's supervision, pediatric patients gain access to clean, licensed medical dispensaries where products are rigorously third-party lab-tested. Dr. Kelly provides precise dosage guidance (including CBD-to-THC ratios and exact milligram schedules) and closely monitors your child's progress to ensure safety and clinical efficacy.
        </p>

        <div class="border-t border-slate-100 pt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-4">
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 italic">
            Read our <a href="/florida-medical-marijuana-card-guide" class="text-brand-primary font-bold hover:underline">Complete Florida Card Guide</a>.
          </p>
          <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://live.vcita.com/site/DrKellyKing/online-scheduling?service=xnfeicu6jent0179" class="bg-brand-accent hover:bg-brand-primary text-white font-bold px-6 py-3 rounded-full text-xs uppercase transition-colors shadow-md active-press">
            Schedule Appointment
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
